properties.Name: GenotypeReserveWord
properties.Description:
Genotype ID reserve words:

where ex:

AA - Ancestral allele
AC - Allele count in genotypes, for each ALT allele 
AD - Total read depth for each allele?
ADF - Read depth for each allele on the forward strand?
ADR - Read depth for each allele on the reverse strand?
AF - Allele frequency for each ALT allele 
AHAP
AN - Total number of alleles in called genotypes?
BQ - RMS base quality?
CICN - Confidence interval around copy number for the segment
CICNADJ - Confidence interval around copy number for the adjacency
CILEN - Confidence interval around the inserted material between breakends
DB - dbSNP membership?
DBRIPID - ID of this element in DBRIP
DBVARID - ID of this element in DBVAR
DGVID - ID of this element in Database of Genomic Variation
DNADJ - Copy number of adjacency
DP - read depth at this position for this sample
DBVARID - ID of this element in DBVAR
DGVID - ID of this element in Database of Genomic Variation
DNADJ - Copy number of adjacency
DP - read depth at this position for this sample
DPADJ - Read Depth of adjacency
EC - comma separated list of expected alternate allele counts for each alternate allele
END - End position (for use with symbolic alleles)?
ENENT - ID of event associated to breakend
FC - Functional Consequence
FT - sample genotype filter indicating if this genotype was "called"
ENENT - ID of event associated to breakend
GL - genotype likelihoods comprised of comma separated floating point log10-scaled likelihoods for all possible genotype 
GLE - genotype likelihoods of heterogeneous ploidy
GQ - conditional genotype quality
GT - genotype, encoded as allele values separated by either of / or |.
H2 - HapMap2 membership
H3 - HapMap3 membership
HAP
HQ - haplotype qualities, two comma separated phred qualities
IMPRECISE  (structural variants) 
MATEID - ID of mate breakends
METRANS - Mobile element transduction info of the form
MQ - RMS mapping quality
MQ0 - Number of MAPQ == 0 reads?
NOVEL
NL- Noise level
NS - Number of samples with data?
PARID - ID of partner breakend
PL - Normalized, Phred-scaled likelihoods for genotypes
PQ - phasing quality
PS - phase set
QD - Variant Confidence/Quality by Depth
SB - Strand bias?
SOMATIC - Somatic mutation (for cancer genomics)?
VALIDATED - Validated by follow-up experiment?
SVLEN - single alternate allele
VF - Variant frequency; the percentage of reads supporting the alternate allele.

Columns.Name: GenotypeReserveWordId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Genotype Reserve Word.

Columns.Description: The description of a Genotype Reserve Word.
